Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Mince a few slices until you have 1 tbsp
minced onion. Core and seed @poblano pepper{1}, then very thinly slice. Peel
@SunGold kiwi{2}, then cut into small cubes. Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1},
then cut into small cubes. Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Halve @lime{1}. Finely
chop @chili pepper{1}, removing ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
sliced onion and poblano. Cook, tossing frequently, until softened and lightly
charred, about ~{8%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan
and set aside.

> TIP: If you're having trouble getting everything to cook, add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, combine kiwis, avocado, half the cilantro, minced onion, and a squeeze
of lime in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add
@beef stir-fry{10%ounce} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp} and toss to combine.
Cook, tossing, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

While steak cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave
on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}.

> TIP: Alternatively, wrap tortillas in foil and warm in oven at 425 degrees for
> 5 minutes.

Fill tortillas with veggies, beef, and salsa. Dollop with @sour cream{¼%cup},
then sprinkle with remaining cilantro and as much chili as you like.